        "title": "Doctor: convert read-only health checks",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis is the first focused follow-up to #80055. It keeps the conversion deliberately low-risk by moving read-only doctor checks into health-check `detect()` findings while leaving repair-heavy areas for later area-specific PRs.\n\nThis PR adds:\n- a checked conversion plan that maps existing doctor contributions to their target health checks;\n- health-check target metadata on doctor contributions;\n- read-only findings for security, browser readiness, workspace suggestions, legacy WhatsApp crontab warnings, and gateway platform notes.\n\n## Behavior addressed\n\nDoctor follow-up conversions are easier to review when each area moves from `run(ctx)` to `detect()` independently. This PR establishes the migration plan and converts read-only checks first, so `doctor --lint` can report these findings without changing repair behavior.\n\n## Staging note\n\nThis PR is stacked conceptually on #80055. The branch includes #80055's base commits plus this first follow-up commit because #80055 has not landed yet. The full conversion branch is intentionally not included here; future follow-ups should be opened area by area after this first slice.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: This PR converts read-only doctor checks to structured health `detect()` findings so `doctor --lint` can report them without repair-mode execution.\n\nReal environment tested: WSL Ubuntu source checkout, branch `doctor-detection-readonly-conversions`, stacked on `doctor-detection-validation`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\npnpm openclaw doctor --lint --only core/doctor/workspace-suggestions --json\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/flows/doctor-health-conversion-plan.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.test.ts src/commands/doctor-lint.test.ts src/commands/doctor-cron.test.ts src/commands/doctor-platform-notes.launchctl-env-overrides.test.ts\ngit diff --check doctor-detection-validation...HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Real CLI output from the WSL source checkout after this patch:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-node.mjs doctor --lint --only core/doctor/workspace-suggestions --json\n{\"ok\":false,\"checksRun\":1,\"checksSkipped\":43,\"findings\":[{\"checkId\":\"core/doctor/workspace-suggestions\",\"severity\":\"info\",\"message\":\"Memory system not found in workspace.\",\"fixHint\":\"Paste this into your agent:\\n\\nInstall the memory system by applying:\\nhttps://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/commit/9ffea23f31ca1df5183b25668f8f814bee0fb34e\\nhttps://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/commit/7d1fee70e76f2f634f1b41fca927ee663914183a\"}]}\n[ELIFECYCLE] Command failed with exit code 1.\n```\n\nFocused Vitest proof also passed: 5 files, 38 tests. `git diff --check` passed with no whitespace/conflict-marker findings.\n\nObserved result after fix: The converted read-only workspace-suggestions check runs through `doctor --lint`, emits a structured `HealthFinding` with checkId `core/doctor/workspace-suggestions`, severity `info`, and a fix hint, without invoking repair mode.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full repository CI and broad Crabbox/Testbox validation were not run locally for this draft; this branch is intended as a narrow stacked follow-up behind #80055.",
